-- SHADOW-SEMANTICS cell D13: definer shadow in VALUE position where the METHOD's
-- arity (2) DIFFERS from the STANDALONE's (1) — issue #410.
--
-- This is the cell the corpus was structurally blind to: D4/D4b are both
-- arity-EQUAL, and when the two arities coincide the emitter's value-position
-- lift can read the arity off the METHOD name and still be accidentally right.
-- With the arities differing that lie became visible: `emitMethodValue` built a
-- 2-arity closure around a body calling the 1-arity standalone, so `map` (which
-- applies ONE arg) got a PARTIAL APPLICATION back instead of an Int. The list
-- then held PAP heap pointers, and `build` printed them as integers —
-- `[70290166652896, ...]` — at exit 0, with no error. SILENT WRONGNESS.
--
-- The result is annotated `List Int` deliberately: that pins THIS bug (the
-- emitter arity lie, fixed by `methValArity`) and keeps the cell independent of
-- the SEPARATE unannotated-requirement-route bug ledgered in d14 (#410's
-- headline repro), which is a typecheck-side NULL element dict.
-- Expected: check/run/build all accept and print [2, 3, 4].
interface Sizeable a where
  size : a -> a -> Int

data Box = Box Int

impl Sizeable Box where
  size (Box a) (Box b) = a + b

size : Int -> Int
size n = n + 1

main =
  let ys = map size [1, 2, 3] : List Int
  println ys
